"Abstract In August 1990 the Computer Misuse Act came into effect. The Act was criticized by many, specifically by those who might have been affected by it but were not, because the Act did not exist at the time they committed the offence. Apart from the criticism, the Act has been welcomed by society, computer users, business companies, Government institutions, police, etc. This article assesses the role of the Computer Crime Unit as the main investigate body of computer misuse within the United Kingdom, and the importance of the Computer Misuse Act 1990 for computer users and for the society as a whole. The article examines the investigation procedure, what the main concerns and problems are, along with the doubts over the effectiveness of the Computer Misuse Act 1990."
